      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): require user intent for chat sessions",
        "body": "Fixes #89760.\n\n## Summary\n- require an explicit user intent token before the WebChat UI helper can create a new session\n- keep sidebar New Chat, chat view New Session, and typed `/new` working by passing that user intent at those action boundaries\n- add a regression test that verifies the helper does not call `sessions.create` or mutate the active conversation without explicit intent\n\n## Behavior addressed\nWebChat startup, reconnect, or bootstrap paths cannot accidentally call the shared new-session helper and emit `sessions.create` reset hooks unless the caller passes explicit user intent. Explicit user actions still create new sessions normally.\n\n## Real environment tested\nLocal macOS worktree `/Users/andy/openclaw-89760` on branch `codex/89760-webchat-no-auto-new`, commit `1e3ccc6da0`.\n\n## Exact steps or command run after this patch\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/app-render.helpers.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-gateway-chat-load.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-chat.test.ts src/gateway/server.sessions.reset-hooks.test.ts ui/src/ui/navigation.browser.test.ts`\n- `git log --format='%h %an <%ae> %s' upstream/main..HEAD`\n\n## Evidence after fix\nThe new `createChatSession` regression calls the helper without `{ source: \"user\" }` and asserts it returns `false`, does not call `createSessionAndRefresh`, preserves `state.sessionKey`, and preserves existing `chatMessages`. Existing explicit-session tests now pass `{ source: \"user\" }` and still verify normal New Chat behavior. The focused Vitest command passed 3 shards: 6 files, 209 tests.\n\n## Observed result after fix\nNo-intent WebChat paths do not call `sessions.create`, so they cannot trigger the gateway reset/archive hook. Explicit New Chat and `/new` paths continue to call session creation.\n\n## What was not tested\nI did not run a live browser reconnect against a production gateway in this local pass. The repo changed-files Crabbox gate could not be run locally because the configured Azure provider needs Azure CLI/login, the Blacksmith Testbox path requires Crabbox >= 0.22.0 while this machine has 0.20.0, and local-container requires Docker, which is not installed on PATH.\n",
